{"word":"ᾠδή","slug":"ᾠδή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ᾠδή</b></el> <el>(ᾠδή, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> for <a href='S:ἀοιδή'><el>ἀοιδή</el></a> as <el>ᾄδω</el> for <a href='S:ἀείδω'><el>ἀείδω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a song, lay, ode</i>, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>lyric poetry</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>song, singing</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}